arts.ttl: Europa League: Ajax defeated by Eintracht Frankfurt
arts.sum: Despite taking an early lead, Ajax fell to a 2-1 loss at home to Eintracht Frankfurt. Ajax came out of the blocks quickly and Brian Brobbey hit the post within two minutes. The striker then headed in the opener eight minutes later. arts.ttl: Frankfurt take down Ajax in a hard-fought Europa League battle
arts.sum: Eintracht Frankfurt went into the 1st leg of the round of 16 in the Europa League against Ajax with high hopes - and were not disappointed! They managed to beat the dutch side 2-1 in a hard-fought and 1st ever match-up thanks to goals from Hugo Larsson and Ellyes Skhiri.

arts.sum: Eintracht Frankfurt's Hugo Ekitiké has said the realisation that "the real pleasure comes from scoring" has turned him into one of the Bundesliga's biggest threats in front of goal this season. I liked being part of play, but I have also understood that real pleasure comes from scoring goals."
